item.title: Office Security Event
item.dc:creator: Matthew Stone
item.description: We are friends with the folks at these events and we can personally vouch for them!

item.title: New York Metro Joint Cyber Security Conference
item.dc:creator: Matthew Stone
item.description: With such an awesome array of professionals under one roof this event had to make our list. If you want to network within information security then this is one event in NYC that you must not miss.

item.title: Cyber Security Summit NYC USA
item.dc:creator: Matthew Stone
item.description: his is a rather high-brow event takes place consistently during UN Week making it the “local Summit” for the producers as it attracts delegates from around the world.

item.title: Healthcare Security Summit: New York
item.dc:creator: Matthew Stone
item.description: If you live and work in the Tri-State area in a Cyber Security and Healthcare capacity then this is a ‘must go’ event.

item.title: Rochester Security Summit
item.dc:creator: Matthew Stone
item.description: These events feature great locally sourced speakers and panels who aim to educate delegates in cyber security and IT.

item.title: The Annual JLCW Conference
item.dc:creator: Matthew Stone
item.description: The Journal of Law and Cyber Warfare symposium brings speakers that are experts with cyber security and cyber warfare from the military, government, private industry, and the public sector.

item.title: NYS ITS (Annual) Cyber Security Conference
item.dc:creator: Matthew Stone
item.description: The conference this year had 1,300 registrants. NYSCSC is one of the more recognized and established cyber security events that happens each year in New York.

item.title: International Conference on Cybersecurity
item.dc:creator: Matthew Stone
item.description: This is an excellent opportunity for those living and working in cyber on the East Coast who’d like to network with some very talented minds.
